Code of Conduct
1. Purpose

This Code of Conduct outlines the standards of behaviour expected from all employees, contractors, and visitors to ensure a safe, respectful, and professional workplace.

2. Professional Behaviour

Treat everyone with respect, fairness, and courtesy

Act honestly and with integrity at all times

Avoid behaviour that could harm the companyâ€™s reputation

3. Respect & Inclusion

No discrimination, harassment, bullying, or victimisation

Respect differences in background, beliefs, and opinions

Maintain a positive and inclusive working environment

4. Communication

Communicate clearly, professionally, and respectfully

Avoid offensive, aggressive, or inappropriate language

Handle disagreements calmly and constructively

5. Health & Safety

Follow all health and safety rules and procedures

Report hazards, accidents, or unsafe behaviour immediately

Do not work under the influence of drugs or alcohol

6. Confidentiality

Protect confidential and sensitive information

Do not share company or client information without authorisation

Follow data protection and privacy laws

7. Conflicts of Interest

Avoid situations where personal interests conflict with work duties

Declare any potential conflicts to management
